===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|sm|Sāmoa}}.  Sa is sacred, forbidden, not allowed.  Sa also mean pertaining to or 'of the'; for example Sa Malietoa is of the family or lineage of Malietoa.  Moa is center or middle, the most inner and deepest part of anything or heart.  It is also a word for chicken.

